Build-Depends: cdbs, debhelper (>= 5)
Standards-Version: 3.7.2

Package: sidux-kernelhacking
Architecture: all
Depends: ssft
Recommends: sidux-modules, dpatch, dpkg-dev, fakeroot, kernel-package
Description: various tools for kernel hacking
 These tools script common tasks while testing kernels, like creating kbuild 
 symlinks, removal of deprecated kernel images and associated drivers or a 
 custom Makefile for /usr/src/.

Package: sidux-modules
Architecture: all
Depends: bzip2, unp, zip, gawk, acx-source, acer-acpi-source, aufs-source, cloop-src (>= 2.05~20060829), fsam7400-source, gspca-source, kqemu-source (>= 1.3.0~pre10-2), linux-wlan-ng-source (>= 0.2.6+svn20061108-1), lirc-modules-source (>= 0.8.0-9+c0.sidux.1), ndiswrapper-source, qc-usb-source (>= 0.6.6-1+c0.sidux.1), rfswitch-source, squashfs-source (>= 1:3.2r2-0+c0.sidux.2)
Recommends: acerhk-source
Suggests: sidux-kernelhacking
Description: meta package for sidux kernel modules
 Depend on commonly used kernel module sources for easy kernel hacking and
 provide easy scripts to unpack those or remove older kernels.
